  <h2 class="sec-title" id="weatherTitle">When to Visit <em>Meghalaya</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="weatherNote" style="margin-bottom:0">Meghalaya is extraordinary in every season but dramatically different. October to April is ideal for clear views, waterfalls still flowing from monsoon rains and the major tribal festivals. The monsoon (May-September) is when Cherrapunji and Mawsynram receive their world-record rainfall — spectacular but challenging. Even the monsoon has its devotees: the living root bridges in full green and the clouds rolling through the valleys are unforgettable.</p>
